            "instructions": "",
            "question_text": "In a class of 12 students, the average marks scored by the students is 60. Average marks scored by the 5 students, who scored the lowest in class, is 55. If every student scored distinct integral marks, then find the maximum possible marks scored by the topper in the class. 1 &nbsp;",
            "options": [
                "",
                "",
                "",
                ""
            ],
            "correct_response": [
                [
                    "4"
                ]
            ],
            "solution": "<div><B>Solution:\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<br>Correct Answer : <b>4</B>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div>As the total marks scored by student is 720 and by bottom 5 students is\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t55 \u00d7 5 = 275.<br>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tAlso, each student has scored the distinct marks and we need to maximise\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tthe score of one individual candidate i.e. the\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\ttopper so, we need to minimise the score of the other students.<br>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tScore of the bottom 5 students will be (53, 54, 55, 56, 57)<br>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tScore of the rest of the students will be (58, 59, 60, 61, 62, 63 and\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t82).<br>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tSo, 4th option.\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</div></div>"
        },
